arch:property.oc:show_val: Further Triple Colonnade collapse and vault collapse.
Phase XII: Robbing and abandonment continue.
Locus 14 Floors in Chambers 2, 3 (Loci 10, and 26) and Locus 25 Threshold between Chambers 2 and 3.
Phase XI: Further collapse post-CE 5th c. Possibly the result of the earthquake of CE 512.

Originally this locus was reserved for the balk left behind in the 2003 excavations. When the trench excavation was moved 8.00 m to the south, it was combined or subsumed by Locus 14. The Munsell color of these deposits is Reddish Yellow 5YR6/6. Most of the inclusions are ashlars and architectural fragments mixed with coarse earth-sand, all of which are unevenly and randomly collapsed. This is a destruction level. The justification for assignment of field phase number is based on the fact that this deposit rests directly up against the walls of Chambers 2 and 3 and over the burning and debris associated above the floor mortar impressions, and with the exception of Locus 20, it postdates any of the architectural features of Room 3 Chambers 2 and 3.
Locus 14 also collapse, fill and debris.
Dimensions: 5.43 m north south-by-3.28m east west-by-2.25 m in depth.
Phase XIII: Major collapses continue into the Islamic period.
Chamber 1, between the West Buttress #1 Locus 6 and the East Buttress #1 Locus 5.
